00:18:28,760 --> 00:18:30,760
We then said this, number four,

244
00:18:30,760 --> 00:18:36,760
Jesus is all the world to me because of His work today.

245
00:18:36,760 --> 00:18:41,760
The Bible teaches us that He is our great High Priest.

246
00:18:41,760 --> 00:18:45,760
The Bible teaches us that He is our Intercessor.

247
00:18:45,760 --> 00:18:49,760
The Bible teaches us that He is our Advocate.

248
00:18:49,760 --> 00:18:51,760
In fact, the Bible teaches us,

249
00:18:51,760 --> 00:18:55,760
and it will be a segue into our final point in our message today,

250
00:18:55,760 --> 00:18:59,760
that He is preparing a place for me.

251
00:18:59,760 --> 00:19:03,760
And so we have looked at these four things

252
00:19:03,760 --> 00:19:05,760
as to why Jesus is all the world to me,

253
00:19:05,760 --> 00:19:08,760
because of who He is, because of His mighty power,

254
00:19:08,760 --> 00:19:10,760
because of His death, burial, and resurrection,

255
00:19:10,760 --> 00:19:12,760
because of His work today.

256
00:19:12,760 --> 00:19:15,760
And number five, if you're continuing to take notes,

257
00:19:15,760 --> 00:19:21,760
I would say this, because He's coming back for me.

258
00:19:21,760 --> 00:19:23,760
Turn to the book of John, if you will,

259
00:19:23,760 --> 00:19:26,760
and we'll be looking at a number of portions of Scripture

260
00:19:26,760 --> 00:19:29,760
as we study through this final point of this lesson,

261
00:19:29,760 --> 00:19:31,760
Jesus is all the world to me.

262
00:19:31,760 --> 00:19:35,760
In John 14, a familiar portion of Scripture,

263
00:19:35,760 --> 00:19:39,760
but I want you to look at the words of this portion

264
00:19:39,760 --> 00:19:43,760
to be encouraged by what Jesus is telling His disciples

265
00:19:43,760 --> 00:19:46,760
and by the truth that is then relayed to us

266
00:19:46,760 --> 00:19:48,760
as the people of God.

267
00:19:48,760 --> 00:19:52,760
We understand that Jesus had given instruction to the disciples

268
00:19:52,760 --> 00:19:56,760
with regard to His soon crucifixion

269
00:19:56,760 --> 00:19:58,760
at the end of chapter 13.

270
00:19:58,760 --> 00:20:01,800
a new commandment that they should love one another

271
00:20:01,800 --> 00:20:04,020
even as He loved them.

272
00:20:04,020 --> 00:20:05,260
And He said this,

273
00:20:05,260 --> 00:20:07,300
"'By this, by your love one for another,

274
00:20:07,300 --> 00:20:10,360
shall all men know that you are My disciples.'"

275
00:20:10,360 --> 00:20:12,240
And what a blessing.

276
00:20:12,240 --> 00:20:14,400
We find that the news of Calvary

277
00:20:14,400 --> 00:20:16,100
and His being glorified

278
00:20:16,100 --> 00:20:18,380
would bring the disciples to a place

279
00:20:18,380 --> 00:20:21,980
of having heavy, troubled hearts, if you will.

280
00:20:21,980 --> 00:20:26,040
And John 14 begins by Jesus saying to these disciples,

281
00:20:26,040 --> 00:20:30,340
"'Let not your heart be troubled.'"

282
00:20:30,340 --> 00:20:32,560
What a great statement.

283
00:20:32,560 --> 00:20:34,480
Let not your heart be troubled.

284
00:20:34,480 --> 00:20:35,480
Why?

285
00:20:35,480 --> 00:20:37,560
I mean, if He just stopped there

286
00:20:37,560 --> 00:20:40,160
and did not give any reason

287
00:20:40,160 --> 00:20:42,920
as to why the heart should not be troubled,

288
00:20:42,920 --> 00:20:45,240
perhaps the disciples would have walked away

289
00:20:45,240 --> 00:20:48,000
with troubled hearts.

290
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:50,600
But Jesus says to these disciples,

291
00:20:50,600 --> 00:20:53,840
"'Let not your heart be troubled.

292
00:20:53,920 --> 00:20:57,440
Ye believe in God, believe also in Me.

293
00:20:57,440 --> 00:21:01,040
In My Father's house are many mansions.

294
00:21:01,040 --> 00:21:04,200
If it were not so, I would have told you.

295
00:21:04,200 --> 00:21:08,960
I go to prepare a place for you.'"

296
00:21:08,960 --> 00:21:10,200
Notice this.

297
00:21:10,200 --> 00:21:13,240
"'And if I go and prepare a place for you,

298
00:21:13,240 --> 00:21:16,360
I will come again

299
00:21:16,360 --> 00:21:19,800
and receive you unto Myself,

300
00:21:19,840 --> 00:21:25,520
that where I am, there ye may be also.'"

301
00:21:25,520 --> 00:21:28,800
Now, I hope that as we look at the words

302
00:21:28,800 --> 00:21:32,640
of this very familiar passage of Scripture,

303
00:21:32,640 --> 00:21:35,360
that your heart is rejoicing

304
00:21:35,360 --> 00:21:38,080
at the very truth that Jesus,

305
00:21:38,080 --> 00:21:39,400
the Son of God,

306
00:21:39,400 --> 00:21:41,440
the King of kings and Lord of lords,

307
00:21:41,440 --> 00:21:45,600
is going to return one day for you.

308
00:21:45,600 --> 00:21:49,080
For all of us collectively as the saints of God,

309
00:21:49,120 --> 00:21:51,160
but just to be mindful of the fact

310
00:21:51,160 --> 00:21:54,520
that individually He's coming for me.

311
00:21:54,520 --> 00:21:56,560
What a blessing!

312
00:21:56,560 --> 00:22:00,440
What joy should fill our hearts!

313
00:22:00,440 --> 00:22:01,960
We think about this statement,

314
00:22:01,960 --> 00:22:05,080
Jesus is all the world to me.

315
00:22:05,080 --> 00:22:08,840
And I hope that you would say that He is.

316
00:22:08,840 --> 00:22:10,520
Perhaps, even as we've mentioned

317
00:22:10,520 --> 00:22:12,280
throughout this series,

318
00:22:12,280 --> 00:22:14,440
there are many other reasons that we could give.

319
00:22:14,440 --> 00:22:16,160
This is not in any way, shape, or form

320
00:22:16,160 --> 00:22:19,320
an exhaustive list.

321
00:22:19,320 --> 00:22:22,600
But we find that as we look at these pages of Scripture

322
00:22:22,600 --> 00:22:27,400
and begin to try to give an answer

323
00:22:27,400 --> 00:22:29,440
as to why Jesus is all the world to me,

324
00:22:29,440 --> 00:22:32,720
think about this, because He's coming back for me.

325
00:22:32,720 --> 00:22:34,120
He loves me so much,

326
00:22:34,120 --> 00:22:37,680
He's going to come back for me.

327
00:22:37,680 --> 00:22:39,440
We look here at this passage

328
00:22:39,440 --> 00:22:43,800
and I believe with all of my heart

329
00:22:43,800 --> 00:22:46,480
that the words that Jesus spoke to the disciples

330
00:22:46,480 --> 00:22:49,400
on this particular day at this moment

331
00:22:49,400 --> 00:22:52,000
were a great source of encouragement.

332
00:22:52,000 --> 00:22:56,160
They would face some difficult moments ahead

333
00:22:56,160 --> 00:23:00,760
as they would watch as their Savior was crucified,

334
00:23:00,760 --> 00:23:03,080
as they would endure the days

335
00:23:03,080 --> 00:23:07,160
in which He was in that tomb.

336
00:23:07,160 --> 00:23:11,320
And then to think of going to that tomb

337
00:23:11,320 --> 00:23:13,760
and finding that it was empty.

338
00:23:13,760 --> 00:23:16,320
The resurrection.

339
00:23:16,320 --> 00:23:20,080
All of the thoughts that would flood their minds.

340
00:23:20,080 --> 00:23:24,360
The emotions that they would deal with.

341
00:23:24,360 --> 00:23:28,320
And then as Jesus was ascended up into heaven

342
00:23:28,320 --> 00:23:30,560
as the book of Acts records for us

343
00:23:30,560 --> 00:23:32,200
in Acts 1,

344
00:23:32,200 --> 00:23:35,400
and the disciples stood there and they beheld.

345
00:23:35,400 --> 00:23:37,280
They saw Him go up into heaven.

346
00:23:37,280 --> 00:23:39,680
The Bible says that they looked steadfastly

347
00:23:39,680 --> 00:23:42,480
toward heaven as He went up.

348
00:23:42,480 --> 00:23:45,440
There were two men that stood by them

349
00:23:45,440 --> 00:23:47,760
in white apparel and they said,

350
00:23:47,760 --> 00:23:52,040
you men of Galilee, why stand ye gazing up into heaven?

351
00:23:52,040 --> 00:23:54,280
This same Jesus,

352
00:23:54,280 --> 00:23:56,560
which has taken up from you into heaven,

353
00:23:56,560 --> 00:23:58,120
shall so come in like manner

354
00:23:58,120 --> 00:24:01,240
as you have seen Him go into heaven.

355
00:24:01,240 --> 00:24:04,800
Now, when these two men that were in white apparel,

356
00:24:04,800 --> 00:24:06,240
angels I suppose,

357
00:24:06,280 --> 00:24:10,840
as they gave this word of encouragement

358
00:24:10,840 --> 00:24:11,960
to these disciples,

359
00:24:11,960 --> 00:24:16,760
as they watched as Jesus was ascended up into heaven,

360
00:24:16,760 --> 00:24:19,160
and they heard the message that said

361
00:24:19,160 --> 00:24:22,800
this same Jesus which has taken up from you into heaven,

362
00:24:22,800 --> 00:24:24,200
shall so come in like manner

363
00:24:24,200 --> 00:24:25,440
as you have seen Him go into heaven.

364
00:24:25,440 --> 00:24:27,720
I just wonder as I study

365
00:24:27,720 --> 00:24:30,000
and I look at this passage of Scripture,

366
00:24:30,000 --> 00:24:35,520
I wonder if their minds race back to that day

367
00:24:35,520 --> 00:24:38,240
where we started in John 14,

368
00:24:38,240 --> 00:24:40,680
when they heard Jesus say,

369
00:24:40,680 --> 00:24:44,320
I will come again and receive you unto Myself.

370
00:24:44,320 --> 00:24:46,720
That where I am, there you may be also.

371
00:24:46,720 --> 00:24:48,839
Perhaps when they heard the message

372
00:24:48,839 --> 00:24:50,600
from these angels,

373
00:24:50,600 --> 00:24:57,000
that they were reminded of what Jesus had said.

374
00:24:57,000 --> 00:24:59,600
How it encouraged them.

375
00:24:59,600 --> 00:25:02,480
How it strengthened them.

376
00:25:02,480 --> 00:25:05,279
I'm mindful of the work that God accomplished

377
00:25:05,279 --> 00:25:08,000
through His servants in the book of Acts

378
00:25:08,000 --> 00:25:10,360
and the early church as you read.

379
00:25:10,360 --> 00:25:12,119
You see all that's taking place

380
00:25:12,119 --> 00:25:13,600
and all of the progress

381
00:25:13,600 --> 00:25:16,480
and the way in which the Gospel is going forward.

382
00:25:16,480 --> 00:25:19,200
And we have to be mindful of the fact

383
00:25:19,200 --> 00:25:22,520
that they were living with a keen awareness

384
00:25:22,520 --> 00:25:26,760
of the soon return of their Lord and Savior Jesus Christ.

385
00:25:26,760 --> 00:25:29,240
I would submit to you today

386
00:25:29,240 --> 00:25:33,240
that the coming of the Lord draweth nigh.

387
00:25:33,240 --> 00:25:36,279
Listen for the trumpet as the songwriter said.

388
00:25:36,279 --> 00:25:39,279
I believe that Jesus is coming soon.

389
00:25:39,279 --> 00:25:41,200
We do not know when He's going to come.

390
00:25:41,200 --> 00:25:43,800
In fact, here even in this same passage of Scripture

391
00:25:43,800 --> 00:25:46,920
when the disciples asked Jesus in v. 6

392
00:25:46,920 --> 00:25:49,320
if He would restore again the Kingdom to Israel,

393
00:25:49,320 --> 00:25:50,240
He said to them,

394
00:25:50,240 --> 00:25:52,600
it's not for them to know the times or seasons

395
00:25:52,600 --> 00:25:55,960
which the Father hath put in His own power.

396
00:25:55,960 --> 00:25:59,440
Our job is to be faithful,

397
00:25:59,440 --> 00:26:01,320
to redeem the time,

398
00:26:01,360 --> 00:26:03,320
because the days are evil.

399
00:26:03,320 --> 00:26:05,920
To be faithful followers of the Lord Jesus Christ.

400
00:26:05,920 --> 00:26:08,000
To be doers of the Word.

401
00:26:08,000 --> 00:26:10,240
To be faithfully engaged in the work of God

402
00:26:10,240 --> 00:26:11,960
even as I preached on Sunday evening

403
00:26:11,960 --> 00:26:14,279
engaged in the work.

404
00:26:14,279 --> 00:26:18,360
We understand the imminent return of Christ.

405
00:26:18,360 --> 00:26:20,920
Because He's coming back for me

406
00:26:20,920 --> 00:26:23,000
is one reason I would give

407
00:26:23,000 --> 00:26:24,720
that Jesus is all the world to me.

408
00:26:24,720 --> 00:26:27,440
Turn to the book of 1 Thessalonians if you will

409
00:26:27,440 --> 00:26:29,680
and listen to what Paul tells these believers

410
00:26:29,680 --> 00:26:32,680
in 1 Thessalonica.

411
00:26:32,680 --> 00:26:35,559
These individuals had been

412
00:26:35,559 --> 00:26:38,320
dealing with all sorts of difficulty

413
00:26:38,320 --> 00:26:41,040
and they were a good church.

414
00:26:41,040 --> 00:26:43,040
A model church.

415
00:26:43,040 --> 00:26:46,360
A faithful group of believers.

416
00:26:46,360 --> 00:26:49,440
And Paul is going to give them instruction here

417
00:26:49,440 --> 00:26:50,720
in 1 Thessalonians 4

418
00:26:50,720 --> 00:26:54,960
that has brought encouragement to my heart many times.

419
00:26:54,960 --> 00:26:56,640
He begins in v. 13, he says,

420
00:26:56,640 --> 00:26:59,839
but I would not have you to be ignorant, brethren,

421
00:26:59,839 --> 00:27:02,200
concerning them which are asleep.

422
00:27:02,200 --> 00:27:04,880
That's referring to those that have died

423
00:27:04,880 --> 00:27:07,600
as we'll find contextually in the passage of Scripture.

424
00:27:07,600 --> 00:27:10,080
We understand that God wants us to be informed.

425
00:27:10,080 --> 00:27:12,040
He does not want us to be ignorant.

426
00:27:12,040 --> 00:27:15,040
He says that ye, sorrow not,

427
00:27:15,040 --> 00:27:19,080
even as others which have no hope.

428
00:27:19,080 --> 00:27:24,680
For if we believe that Jesus died and rose again,

429
00:27:24,720 --> 00:27:28,640
even so, them also which sleep in Jesus

430
00:27:28,640 --> 00:27:32,160
will God bring with Him.

431
00:27:32,160 --> 00:27:35,160
For this we say unto you by the word of the Lord,

432
00:27:35,160 --> 00:27:37,040
that we which are alive and remain

433
00:27:37,040 --> 00:27:38,559
unto the coming of the Lord

434
00:27:38,559 --> 00:27:41,920
shall not prevent them which are asleep.

435
00:27:41,920 --> 00:27:44,720
For the Lord Himself shall descend from heaven

436
00:27:44,720 --> 00:27:47,760
with a shout, with the voice of the archangel,

437
00:27:47,760 --> 00:27:49,559
and with the trump of God.

438
00:27:49,559 --> 00:27:51,600
The dead in Christ shall rise first.

439
00:27:51,600 --> 00:27:54,320
Then, we which are alive and remain

440
00:27:54,360 --> 00:27:57,559
shall be caught up together with them in the clouds

441
00:27:57,559 --> 00:27:59,520
to meet the Lord in the air.

442
00:27:59,520 --> 00:28:03,640
And so shall we ever be with the Lord.

443
00:28:03,640 --> 00:28:06,480
It ends with these words, verse 18,

444
00:28:06,480 --> 00:28:11,080
Wherefore, comfort one another with these words.

445
00:28:11,080 --> 00:28:13,680
How comforting these words are.

446
00:28:13,680 --> 00:28:16,200
How encouraging these words are

447
00:28:16,200 --> 00:28:20,240
to understand that Jesus is going to return

448
00:28:20,240 --> 00:28:23,080
and to think about the truth of verse 17.

449
00:28:23,160 --> 00:28:27,160
I don't know, we don't know if we'll be alive at the rapture

450
00:28:27,160 --> 00:28:29,839
or if we'll be one of those that is mentioned earlier

451
00:28:29,839 --> 00:28:32,840
that the dead in Christ shall rise first.

452
00:28:32,840 --> 00:28:36,400
We're not sure, but the excitement would be

453
00:28:36,400 --> 00:28:38,640
if we were alive, verse 17,

454
00:28:38,640 --> 00:28:41,679
then we which are alive and remain,

455
00:28:41,679 --> 00:28:43,320
notice what it says,

456
00:28:43,320 --> 00:28:46,799
shall be caught up together with them,

457
00:28:46,799 --> 00:28:49,160
that's the saints that have died in Christ,

458
00:28:49,160 --> 00:28:50,679
the dead in Christ,

459
00:28:50,679 --> 00:28:52,919
in the clouds, notice this,

460
00:28:52,919 --> 00:28:57,359
to meet the Lord in the air.

461
00:28:57,359 --> 00:28:58,960
And then it says this,

462
00:28:58,960 --> 00:29:04,239
And so shall we ever be with the Lord.

463
00:29:04,239 --> 00:29:06,440
For all of eternity,

464
00:29:06,440 --> 00:29:09,840
we'll have the great privilege of being with our Savior.

465
00:29:09,840 --> 00:29:12,119
Isn't that wonderful?

466
00:29:12,119 --> 00:29:15,080
It's encouraging. It's comforting.

467
00:29:15,080 --> 00:29:17,679
It causes us to live life

468
00:29:17,679 --> 00:29:20,400
and face the challenges of life

469
00:29:20,400 --> 00:29:22,799
in a different manner.

470
00:29:22,919 --> 00:29:26,280
Because we understand that we are strangers in pilgrims, right?

471
00:29:26,280 --> 00:29:27,840
This world is not my home.

472
00:29:27,840 --> 00:29:30,919
I'm just a passing through.

473
00:29:30,919 --> 00:29:33,720
I'm not home, but I'm going home.

474
00:29:33,720 --> 00:29:35,400
My citizenship is in heaven.

475
00:29:35,400 --> 00:29:37,479
We are ambassadors,

476
00:29:37,479 --> 00:29:40,479
as Paul says to the church in Corinth.

477
00:29:40,479 --> 00:29:42,880
What a great privilege it is to know

478
00:29:42,880 --> 00:29:45,679
that He's coming back for me.

479
00:29:45,679 --> 00:29:47,640
The Bible continues to give us truth.

480
00:29:47,640 --> 00:29:50,840
Turn to the book of Hebrews, if you will,

481
00:29:50,880 --> 00:29:54,799
in regard to this promised return.

482
00:29:54,799 --> 00:29:58,080
As we think about the promised return of our Savior,

483
00:29:58,080 --> 00:29:59,080
we find that He...

484
00:29:59,080 --> 00:30:02,020
Hebrews 9 and verse number 27,

485
00:30:02,020 --> 00:30:03,820
a verse that we often will use

486
00:30:03,820 --> 00:30:05,280
when we're speaking to people

487
00:30:05,280 --> 00:30:07,720
about their need for Christ and for salvation.

488
00:30:07,720 --> 00:30:08,320
This is,

489
00:30:08,320 --> 00:30:10,240
"...as it is appointed unto men once to die,

490
00:30:10,240 --> 00:30:12,160
but after this the judgment we find..."

491
00:30:12,160 --> 00:30:13,080
Verse 28,

492
00:30:13,080 --> 00:30:23,280
"...so Christ was once offered

493
00:30:23,280 --> 00:30:26,000
to bear the sins of many,

494
00:30:26,000 --> 00:30:28,560
and unto them that look for Him

495
00:30:28,560 --> 00:30:31,240
shall He appear the second time

496
00:30:31,240 --> 00:30:34,760
without sin unto salvation."

497
00:30:34,760 --> 00:30:37,440
You notice that it says that He shall appear.

498
00:30:37,440 --> 00:30:38,920
And I'm so thankful.

