00:31:05,600 --> 00:31:06,840
that God sent forth His Son

513
00:31:06,840 --> 00:31:08,440
made of a woman made under the law

514
00:31:08,440 --> 00:31:10,360
to redeem them that were under the law

515
00:31:10,360 --> 00:31:12,320
that would receive the adoption of sons.

516
00:31:12,320 --> 00:31:13,320
How did He do that?

517
00:31:13,320 --> 00:31:15,840
Redemption is through the blood of Christ.

518
00:31:15,840 --> 00:31:17,640
And so sin has been dealt with

519
00:31:17,640 --> 00:31:20,600
based on His first coming.

520
00:31:20,600 --> 00:31:22,040
At His second coming,

521
00:31:22,040 --> 00:31:24,000
He's not going to have to deal with sin

522
00:31:24,000 --> 00:31:26,440
as far as the payment for sin.

523
00:31:26,960 --> 00:31:30,240
And we find that we will have that privilege

524
00:31:30,240 --> 00:31:32,840
at the rapture of the church

525
00:31:32,840 --> 00:31:34,280
of being able to be with Him

526
00:31:34,280 --> 00:31:35,560
for all of eternity.

527
00:31:35,560 --> 00:31:37,640
In chapter 10 of the book of Hebrews,

528
00:31:37,640 --> 00:31:42,320
in verse 37, notice what the Bible says.

529
00:31:42,320 --> 00:31:44,760
For yet a little while,

530
00:31:44,760 --> 00:31:49,280
and He that shall come will come,

531
00:31:49,280 --> 00:31:53,880
and will not tarry.

532
00:31:53,880 --> 00:31:56,360
Listen, Jesus came right on time

533
00:31:56,360 --> 00:31:58,200
the first time.

534
00:31:58,200 --> 00:31:59,640
When the fullness of time was come,

535
00:31:59,640 --> 00:32:00,800
God sent forth His Son.

536
00:32:00,800 --> 00:32:03,160
I just referenced that in Galatians 4

537
00:32:03,160 --> 00:32:05,720
in verse number 4.

538
00:32:05,720 --> 00:32:08,440
He's coming back right on time.

539
00:32:08,440 --> 00:32:10,120
Sometimes we would say,

540
00:32:10,120 --> 00:32:12,760
I wish it was sooner than later.

541
00:32:12,760 --> 00:32:14,600
I'm ready for Him to come today.

542
00:32:14,600 --> 00:32:16,960
I feel you. I understand.

543
00:32:16,960 --> 00:32:18,920
But the reality is that He's coming

544
00:32:18,920 --> 00:32:19,800
right on time.

545
00:32:19,800 --> 00:32:23,360
And His time is perfect.

546
00:32:23,360 --> 00:32:25,520
His timing is perfect.

547
00:32:25,560 --> 00:32:27,480
We see that throughout the pages of Scripture.

548
00:32:27,480 --> 00:32:29,480
We don't have time to deal with that.

549
00:32:29,480 --> 00:32:32,160
But we understand that His timing is perfect.

550
00:32:32,160 --> 00:32:34,360
And I love that the Bible says

551
00:32:34,360 --> 00:32:37,480
that yet a little while,

552
00:32:37,480 --> 00:32:41,280
and He that shall come will come,

553
00:32:41,280 --> 00:32:45,720
and will not tarry.

554
00:32:45,720 --> 00:32:50,960
Notice in James chapter 5,

555
00:32:50,960 --> 00:32:52,320
we're going to make our way through

556
00:32:52,320 --> 00:32:54,240
a few more portions of Scripture

557
00:32:54,240 --> 00:32:55,880
that end in the book of 1 John.

558
00:32:55,880 --> 00:32:58,680
And Lord willing, it will help us

559
00:32:58,680 --> 00:33:00,080
to not only be encouraged,

560
00:33:00,080 --> 00:33:03,000
but challenged as we're mindful

561
00:33:03,000 --> 00:33:07,000
of this truth that Jesus is coming back for me.

562
00:33:07,000 --> 00:33:11,520
In James 5, notice in verse 7,

563
00:33:11,520 --> 00:33:14,160
Be patient therefore, brethren,

564
00:33:14,160 --> 00:33:16,360
unto the coming of the Lord.

565
00:33:16,360 --> 00:33:19,600
Behold, the husbandman waiteth

566
00:33:19,600 --> 00:33:22,480
for the precious fruit of the earth

567
00:33:22,520 --> 00:33:25,120
and hath long patience for it

568
00:33:25,120 --> 00:33:28,880
until he receive the early and latter rain.

569
00:33:28,880 --> 00:33:31,360
Be ye also patient.

570
00:33:31,360 --> 00:33:33,800
Establish your hearts.

571
00:33:33,800 --> 00:33:38,560
For the coming of the Lord draweth nigh.

572
00:33:38,560 --> 00:33:41,680
As we look at verse 7 and understand

573
00:33:41,680 --> 00:33:43,200
even as we just mentioned

574
00:33:43,200 --> 00:33:45,960
that God's timing is perfect,

575
00:33:45,960 --> 00:33:48,400
it tells us that the husbandman

576
00:33:48,400 --> 00:33:51,440
waiteth for the precious fruit of the earth

577
00:33:51,440 --> 00:33:53,600
and hath long patience for it.

578
00:33:53,600 --> 00:33:55,800
We'd understand the picture there

579
00:33:55,800 --> 00:34:00,080
of the agriculture reference that is given.

580
00:34:00,080 --> 00:34:03,320
The way in which you sow, you plant,

581
00:34:03,320 --> 00:34:06,400
you seek to cultivate,

582
00:34:06,400 --> 00:34:08,080
and all that you do,

583
00:34:08,080 --> 00:34:10,120
you water, etc.

584
00:34:10,120 --> 00:34:12,240
So that you can receive that harvest.

585
00:34:12,240 --> 00:34:15,200
And there's a requirement of patience

586
00:34:15,200 --> 00:34:17,720
in receiving that harvest.

587
00:34:17,720 --> 00:34:20,200
You don't plant today and reap tomorrow.

588
00:34:20,240 --> 00:34:22,320
It doesn't work that way.

589
00:34:22,320 --> 00:34:24,920
We think about the precious fruit of the earth

590
00:34:24,920 --> 00:34:26,720
and we think about the souls

591
00:34:26,720 --> 00:34:27,840
that would be saved

592
00:34:27,840 --> 00:34:30,720
and just the joy of being able

593
00:34:30,720 --> 00:34:33,720
to have one more person

594
00:34:33,720 --> 00:34:36,440
have their name written in the Book of Life.

595
00:34:36,440 --> 00:34:37,960
What a joy.

596
00:34:37,960 --> 00:34:40,120
The Bible tells us in 2 Peter 3,

597
00:34:40,120 --> 00:34:42,080
really as we think about that thought here

598
00:34:42,080 --> 00:34:45,600
in James 5 and look at 2 Peter 3,

599
00:34:45,600 --> 00:34:49,480
remember there were various scoffers

600
00:34:49,480 --> 00:34:51,160
and things that were going on

601
00:34:51,160 --> 00:34:52,720
during this particular time.

602
00:34:52,720 --> 00:34:54,560
We see that it continues even today.

603
00:34:54,560 --> 00:34:56,560
And one of the things that they would say

604
00:34:56,560 --> 00:34:58,720
is where's the promise of His coming?

605
00:34:58,720 --> 00:35:00,280
So thankful that He did promise

606
00:35:00,280 --> 00:35:01,760
that He was coming.

607
00:35:01,760 --> 00:35:04,160
And because He has not come

608
00:35:04,160 --> 00:35:07,240
does not void the promise.

609
00:35:07,240 --> 00:35:09,160
Because He did not say the day

610
00:35:09,160 --> 00:35:10,760
or the hour that He would come.

611
00:35:10,760 --> 00:35:14,400
He said He's coming and He's coming right on time.

612
00:35:14,400 --> 00:35:16,720
And we find that Peter encouraged the believers

613
00:35:16,720 --> 00:35:18,680
by telling them this in verse 9

614
00:35:18,680 --> 00:35:20,320
of 2 Peter 3,

615
00:35:20,320 --> 00:35:23,840
the Lord is not slack concerning His promise,

616
00:35:23,840 --> 00:35:26,160
as some men count slackness.

617
00:35:26,160 --> 00:35:28,600
But as longsuffering to us were,

618
00:35:28,600 --> 00:35:32,040
not willing that any should perish,

619
00:35:32,040 --> 00:35:34,840
but that all should come to repentance.

620
00:35:34,840 --> 00:35:36,880
I'm so thankful that the Lord is not slack

621
00:35:36,880 --> 00:35:38,440
concerning His promise.

622
00:35:38,440 --> 00:35:40,200
You understand that God is not a man,

623
00:35:40,200 --> 00:35:42,000
that He should lie.

624
00:35:42,000 --> 00:35:44,760
We understand as we look at the pages of Scripture

625
00:35:44,760 --> 00:35:46,840
and we are mindful of the truth

626
00:35:46,840 --> 00:35:51,440
that our God is just a faithful God.

627
00:35:51,440 --> 00:35:52,760
He's trustworthy.

628
00:35:52,760 --> 00:35:54,560
He is dependable.

629
00:35:54,560 --> 00:35:57,280
Paul said it this way in 2 Corinthians 1

630
00:35:57,280 --> 00:35:58,280
and verse 20,

631
00:35:58,280 --> 00:36:01,960
for all the promises of God in Him are yea,

632
00:36:01,960 --> 00:36:04,040
and in Him, amen,

633
00:36:04,040 --> 00:36:08,480
unto the glory of God by us.

634
00:36:08,480 --> 00:36:11,000
Paul, as he's writing to Titus,

635
00:36:11,000 --> 00:36:12,920
says this in hope of eternal life,

636
00:36:12,920 --> 00:36:15,160
which God that cannot lie

637
00:36:15,160 --> 00:36:17,800
promised before the world began.

638
00:36:17,800 --> 00:36:23,400
Listen, God has given many, many promises.

639
00:36:23,400 --> 00:36:25,480
You find that He always does

640
00:36:25,480 --> 00:36:28,000
what He says He will do.

641
00:36:28,000 --> 00:36:29,360
I'm mindful of that very truth

642
00:36:29,360 --> 00:36:31,240
even as we're studying through the book of Genesis

643
00:36:31,240 --> 00:36:33,520
on Sunday evenings.

644
00:36:33,520 --> 00:36:37,040
You see how God had made promises.

645
00:36:37,040 --> 00:36:40,400
And He always does what He says He will do.

646
00:36:40,400 --> 00:36:42,320
We serve a faithful God.

647
00:36:42,360 --> 00:36:45,240
He's promised to come back for us.

648
00:36:45,240 --> 00:36:48,560
And we can rest in that promise

649
00:36:48,560 --> 00:36:52,040
knowing that He will return.

650
00:36:52,040 --> 00:36:56,560
Finish with me in 1 John 2.

651
00:36:56,560 --> 00:36:58,320
We'll read through the end of the chapter

652
00:36:58,320 --> 00:37:03,480
and into the first few verses of the 3rd chapter.

653
00:37:03,480 --> 00:37:06,080
In 1 John 2 and verse 28,

654
00:37:06,080 --> 00:37:06,920
the Bible says,

655
00:37:06,920 --> 00:37:11,320
"...now little children abide in Him,

656
00:37:11,320 --> 00:37:14,440
that when He shall appear..."

657
00:37:14,440 --> 00:37:16,560
Do you understand the language that we've been using

658
00:37:16,560 --> 00:37:18,680
as we've studied the pages of Scripture,

659
00:37:18,680 --> 00:37:20,560
the various portions that we've looked at

660
00:37:20,560 --> 00:37:22,640
in this study?

661
00:37:22,640 --> 00:37:25,680
It's never terminology or verbiage

662
00:37:25,680 --> 00:37:28,680
that would have any indication

663
00:37:28,680 --> 00:37:32,200
of uncertainty.

664
00:37:32,200 --> 00:37:35,840
Rather, each passage that we've looked to

665
00:37:35,880 --> 00:37:38,680
has revealed to us through the verbiage that is used

666
00:37:38,680 --> 00:37:41,800
the absolute certainty.

667
00:37:41,800 --> 00:37:43,560
When He shall appear.

668
00:37:43,560 --> 00:37:45,480
Not if He shall appear,

669
00:37:45,480 --> 00:37:48,280
but when He shall appear.

670
00:37:48,280 --> 00:37:50,440
The Bible says, "...and now little children abide in Him,

671
00:37:50,440 --> 00:37:53,200
that when He shall appear,

672
00:37:53,200 --> 00:37:55,440
we may have confidence..."

673
00:37:55,440 --> 00:37:57,040
Notice this.

674
00:37:57,040 --> 00:38:04,160
"...and not be ashamed before Him at His coming."

675
00:38:04,200 --> 00:38:08,080
I hope that there's not one among us

676
00:38:08,080 --> 00:38:12,160
that would be ashamed at the coming of the Lord.

677
00:38:12,160 --> 00:38:14,800
It's possible though.

678
00:38:14,800 --> 00:38:16,880
One of my duties as a pastor

679
00:38:16,880 --> 00:38:21,800
is to teach, to feed the flock of God.

680
00:38:21,800 --> 00:38:23,000
To warn.

681
00:38:23,000 --> 00:38:24,880
To instruct.

682
00:38:24,880 --> 00:38:28,880
I would say this, it's to prepare you.

683
00:38:28,880 --> 00:38:31,840
To prepare you for the coming of the Lord.

684
00:38:31,840 --> 00:38:33,360
To prepare you for the standing

685
00:38:33,360 --> 00:38:37,520
at the behemoth seat of Christ.

686
00:38:37,520 --> 00:38:39,520
To give you instruction from the Word of God.

687
00:38:39,520 --> 00:38:42,200
I cannot make you obey the Word of God.

688
00:38:42,200 --> 00:38:45,600
It would not be right for me to do that.

689
00:38:45,600 --> 00:38:47,840
I can simply preach and teach the truth

690
00:38:47,840 --> 00:38:49,559
that is contained within this Word

691
00:38:49,559 --> 00:38:52,640
and encourage you.

692
00:38:52,640 --> 00:38:55,880
Tell you that it's in your best interest to obey.

693
00:38:55,880 --> 00:38:59,920
To be doers of the Word and not hearers only.

694
00:38:59,920 --> 00:39:04,040
The Bible says that we would be not ashamed

695
00:39:04,040 --> 00:39:07,280
before Him at His coming.

696
00:39:07,280 --> 00:39:09,600
I hope that not one of us,

697
00:39:09,600 --> 00:39:10,880
a Fellowship Baptist church,

698
00:39:10,880 --> 00:39:14,760
would be ashamed at His appearing.

699
00:39:14,760 --> 00:39:16,360
The Bible continues in v. 29,

700
00:39:16,360 --> 00:39:19,160
"...if you know that He is righteous,

701
00:39:19,160 --> 00:39:21,600
you know that everyone that doeth righteousness

702
00:39:21,600 --> 00:39:22,720
is born of Him."

703
00:39:22,720 --> 00:39:25,320
Notice v. 1 of chapter 3.

704
00:39:25,320 --> 00:39:28,239
"...Behold, what manner of love

705
00:39:28,280 --> 00:39:31,280
does the Father have bestowed upon us

706
00:39:31,280 --> 00:39:36,640
that we should be called the sons of God."

707
00:39:36,640 --> 00:39:38,960
Isn't that a precious title?

708
00:39:38,960 --> 00:39:41,119
We're the sons of God.

709
00:39:41,119 --> 00:39:43,200
Children of the King.

710
00:39:43,200 --> 00:39:45,559
I'm a child of the King.

711
00:39:45,559 --> 00:39:48,679
Complete in Christ.

712
00:39:48,679 --> 00:39:50,600
"...Therefore, the world knoweth us not

713
00:39:50,600 --> 00:39:54,000
because it knew Him not."

714
00:39:54,000 --> 00:39:59,000
Beloved, now are we the sons of God.

715
00:39:59,000 --> 00:40:02,559
And it doth not yet appear what we shall be,

716
00:40:02,559 --> 00:40:07,960
but we know that when he shall appear,

717
00:40:07,960 --> 00:40:12,960
we shall be like him, for we shall see him as he is.

718
00:40:12,960 --> 00:40:18,760
And every man that hath this hope in him purifieth himself

719
00:40:18,760 --> 00:40:23,280
even as he is pure."

720
00:40:23,280 --> 00:40:25,760
It's important that we understand that word hope

721
00:40:25,760 --> 00:40:30,079
in verse number 3 of chapter 3.

722
00:40:30,079 --> 00:40:33,360
The word hope is used throughout the Bible.

723
00:40:33,360 --> 00:40:36,319
In fact, Paul, as he's writing to Titus in Titus 2,

724
00:40:36,319 --> 00:40:38,439
talks about the blessed hope and glorious appearing

725
00:40:38,439 --> 00:40:42,240
of our great God and Savior, the Lord Jesus Christ.

726
00:40:42,240 --> 00:40:47,799
We read about the word hope, and the biblical definition

727
00:40:47,799 --> 00:40:52,000
of that word hope is to have that confidence.

728
00:40:52,000 --> 00:40:55,000
Too often, we may allow the definitions

729
00:40:55,000 --> 00:40:58,400
that are common today for our vocabulary

730
00:40:58,400 --> 00:41:02,279
to influence our understanding of the Bible.

731
00:41:02,279 --> 00:41:06,440
We might use that word hope today as a wishful thought,

732
00:41:06,440 --> 00:41:09,040
wishful thinking kind of a manner.

733
00:41:09,040 --> 00:41:13,360
I hope this happens, or I hope that happens.

734
00:41:13,360 --> 00:41:16,919
But biblical hope is not in that vein.

735
00:41:16,919 --> 00:41:20,720
Biblical hope is confidence.

736
00:41:20,720 --> 00:41:22,160
What is it confident of?

737
00:41:22,199 --> 00:41:25,360
It's confident of the promise of God.

738
00:41:25,360 --> 00:41:26,599
We have this hope.

739
00:41:26,599 --> 00:41:28,919
We have this confidence.

740
00:41:28,919 --> 00:41:32,360
Because he said, why is it called the blessed hope?

741
00:41:32,360 --> 00:41:34,000
Because it's based upon the truth

742
00:41:34,000 --> 00:41:39,400
that God gave us, the very words that Jesus spoke.

743
00:41:39,400 --> 00:41:41,239
And so we see that the Bible says

744
00:41:41,239 --> 00:41:45,919
that we have this hope, and every man that hath this hope.

745
00:41:45,919 --> 00:41:48,080
If you've been born again, if you're a child of God,

746
00:41:48,080 --> 00:41:49,959
if you're a son of God, as it says here,

747
00:41:49,959 --> 00:41:52,080
and you understand the teaching of Scripture,

748
00:41:52,080 --> 00:41:54,559
if you understand that He is going to appear,

749
00:41:54,559 --> 00:41:57,160
and you have that hope, notice the impact

750
00:41:57,160 --> 00:41:58,760
that it has on our lives.

751
00:41:58,760 --> 00:42:04,199
It says this, that He purifies Himself, even as He is pure.

752
00:42:08,039 --> 00:42:14,520
Having that desire to be clean, to be pure.

753
00:42:14,520 --> 00:42:16,320
We understand that we'll never reach a place

754
00:42:16,320 --> 00:42:17,559
of sinless perfection.

755
00:42:20,119 --> 00:42:21,880
But we understand that we have an advocate

756
00:42:21,880 --> 00:42:23,559
with the Father.

757
00:42:23,559 --> 00:42:29,720
We understand that our God is a God of forgiveness.

758
00:42:29,720 --> 00:42:33,919
And we think about this truth of walking in the Spirit,

759
00:42:33,919 --> 00:42:36,679
walking in the light as He is in the light.

760
00:42:36,679 --> 00:42:40,399
This idea of purifying Himself, the idea of desiring

761
00:42:40,399 --> 00:42:43,320
to be clean, to have no sin, to have no,

762
00:42:43,320 --> 00:42:44,800
as the songwriter put it this way,

763
00:42:44,800 --> 00:42:49,479
nothing between my soul and my Savior.

764
00:42:49,479 --> 00:42:56,199
And we understand that the connection, if you will,

765
00:42:56,199 --> 00:43:01,240
between 1 John 2, 28 and 1 John 3, verse number 3,

766
00:43:01,240 --> 00:43:04,440
the way in which we can prevent being ashamed before Him

767
00:43:04,440 --> 00:43:08,520
at His coming is by purifying ourselves.

768
00:43:08,520 --> 00:43:09,960
I know I've mentioned this before,

769
00:43:09,960 --> 00:43:13,039
but Holly was part of a music group in college.

770
00:43:13,039 --> 00:43:15,520
And they would go and sing in various churches.

771
00:43:15,520 --> 00:43:19,440
And one of the songs that they sang one of the years

772
00:43:19,440 --> 00:43:23,559
that she was in the group was, Are You Ready?

773
00:43:23,559 --> 00:43:26,240
And it would ask the question repeatedly through the song,

774
00:43:26,240 --> 00:43:27,000
are you ready?

775
00:43:27,000 --> 00:43:27,679
Are you ready?

776
00:43:27,679 --> 00:43:28,160
Are you ready?

777
00:43:28,160 --> 00:43:28,720
Are you ready?

778
00:43:28,720 --> 00:43:31,960
Are you ready for the coming of the Lord?

779
00:43:31,960 --> 00:43:34,839
Are you ready?

780
00:43:34,839 --> 00:43:37,440
I know that oftentimes we say, Lord,

781
00:43:37,440 --> 00:43:40,320
we're ready for You to come back, but are we?

